# linBoard API — Environment Variables

See [`.env.linos.example`](../../.env.linos.example) at the repo root for the complete configuration.

For local development, copy and fill in relevant variables:

```bash
cp ../../.env.linos.example .env
```

Core variables for API:

```
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=4001
LOG_LEVEL=info
CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS=http://localhost:4000,http://dashboard.lan
LINOS_DASHBOARD_HOST=dashboard.lan
```

Optional (Home Assistant integration for timer light feedback):

```
LINOS_HA_URL=http://<YOUR_HA_HOST>:8123
LINOS_HA_TOKEN=<YOUR_HA_TOKEN>
LINOS_NOTIFICATION_LIGHT_ENTITIES=light.hallway,light.desk
```

In production (Docker), environment variables are sourced from `.env.linos` at the repo root.
